ROGUE - AKAI EDITION
====================

An ASCII dungeon crawler built with TypeScript + HTML5 Canvas.
Inspired by the original Rogue (1980). Runs in any modern browser.
Play at: https://unluckylisp.com/games/rogue/


FEATURES
--------

  Procedural Dungeons
    - New map every run and every descent
    - BSP room placement with L-shaped corridors
    - 4 biomes across 28 floors, each with unique hazards and monsters

  Field of View
    - Recursive shadowcasting (radius 9)
    - Explored tiles stay visible in dimmed "memory" state
    - Monsters only visible within line of sight

  Turn-Based Combat
    - Bump into monsters to attack
    - Damage: random(1..attack) - defense, minimum 1
    - Monsters move and attack each player turn

  Two Game Modes
    Classic   - permadeath, single run, auto-saves every 5 turns
    Roguelike - gold persists across runs; spend in The Village lobby
                on permanent meta upgrades (Vitality / Strength / Fortitude)
                and cosmetic skins

  Biomes
    The Dungeon      Floors  1-7    standard stone dungeon
    Frozen Caverns   Floors  8-14   ice patches cause sliding
    The Slime Pits   Floors 15-21   slime pools drain 1 HP/turn
    The Inferno      Floors 22-28   lava floors drain 3 HP/turn

  Monsters (16 types, biome-appropriate)
    Dungeon:  Rat, Goblin, Orc, Troll, Dragon
    Ice:      Frost Wolf, Yeti, Ice Elemental, Ice Dragon (freezes player)
    Slime:    Slime, Jelly, Slime Lord
    Inferno:  Ember Spirit, Drake, Fire Demon, Fire Dragon (creates lava)

  Items
    !   Health Potion       heal 10-20 HP
    ◆   Super Mushroom      heal 25-40 HP
    ¢   Coin Bag            +gold or +XP depending on mode
    [   Shield              +2 DEF permanent
    )   Weapon              procedural; replaces equipped weapon
    /   Lightning Scroll    zap nearest monster 15-25 dmg
    ♠   Fire Flower         hits all visible monsters 8-14 each
    ☻   Bomb                hits all adjacent monsters 10-18 each
    :   Lantern             +5 FOV radius for 15 turns
    *   Star                3 turns of invincibility
    ?   Magic Map           reveals entire floor
    *   Ice Bomb            freezes all visible monsters 2 turns

  Skins (Roguelike)
    Classic, Pea Soup, Amber, Copper, Blood Moon, Oceanic, Amethyst

  Clan Primer
    In-game codex that tracks monster encounters, kills, discovered
    items, and hazards across all runs

  HUD
    HP bar (color-coded), ATK, DEF, level, XP, depth, turn counter
    Equipped weapon name
    Message log (last 6 events)


CONTROLS
--------

  Move          WASD  |  Arrow Keys  |  Numpad 8 4 6 2
  Diagonal      Y U B N  (top-left, top-right, bot-left, bot-right)
                Numpad 7 9 1 3
  Vim keys      H J K L  (left down up right)
  Wait          .  or  Numpad 5
  Pick up item  G
  Descend       >  (standing on stairs tile)
  Pause / menu  Escape
  Clan Primer   C  (during play)


HOW TO RUN
----------

  npm install
  npm run dev

  Open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.

  Production build:
  npm run build   (output to dist/)


PROJECT LAYOUT
--------------

  src/
    types.ts        shared interfaces and value enums
    dungeon.ts      BSP procedural map generation
    fov.ts          recursive shadowcasting
    entities.ts     player/monster/item factories and spawn logic
    combat.ts       attack rolls, item use, monster AI
    meta.ts         roguelike meta-progression and skin system
    save.ts         classic-mode save/load
    renderer.ts     canvas renderer, HUD, all screens
    game.ts         game loop, state, input handling
    themes.ts       color palette themes
    audio.ts        sound effects
    biomes.ts       biome definitions and palettes
    discoveries.ts  cross-run discovery log
    main.ts         entry point


TECH STACK
----------

  TypeScript 5, Vite 8, HTML5 Canvas API
  No runtime dependencies


GITHUB
